label: AB2C2D5E_tP11_123_a_h_h_ci_b-001
title: YBaCuFeO$_{5}$ Structure
comments:
The copper and iron (2h) sites are each only 50\% occupied. 
 If we remove the copper atoms and fully occupy the iron sites this structure is very similar to the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB2C5D_oP18_51_a_2f_2efj_c-001}{$Pmma$ (\#51)} and \href{current_web_home_dir/AB2C5D_oP9_47_a_l_gjk_b-001}{$Pmmm$ (\#47)} structures of YBaFe$_{2}$O$_{5}$, and in our opinion is quite likely the high-temperature phase of that compound.
